erything from clothes and home furnishings to cookware and food. In A Rainbow Palate, Carolyn Cobbold explores how the widespread use of new chemical substances influenced perceptions and understanding of food, science, and technology, as well as trust in science and scientists. Because the new dyes were among the earliest contested chemical additives in food, the battles over their use offer striking insights and parallels into today’s international struggles surrounding chemical, food, and trade regulation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aAdulterations. 0aColoring matter in food. 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aEurope.  aUS.  aadulteration.  achemicals.  achemists.  acoal tar dyes.  afood.  anineteenth century.  aregulation.  atesting.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070481508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2020z9783110704617oZDB-23-DEI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUChP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069309640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226727196423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226727196.jpg  a978-3-11-069309-6  UChP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070481-5  EBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEIb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020